Runa Standard Library Stub: AI Communications Broadcast Module

This stub provides complete type definitions and function signatures for the AI communications broadcast module,
enabling compiler semantic analysis and type checking. Extracted from actual implementation
file runa/src/stdlib/ai/comms/broadcast.runa.

Module: AI Communications Broadcast System
Purpose: Production-ready broadcast communication framework for one-to-many message distribution
Dependencies: core_types, crypto, time, uuid
:End Note

Note: Broadcast System Types
Type BroadcastTopic is Dictionary with:
    topic_id as String
    name as String
    description as String
    namespace as String
    created_time as Float
    creator_id as String
    access_control as Dictionary[String, Boolean]
    retention_policy as Dictionary[String, Any]
    delivery_guarantees as List[String]
    max_message_size as Integer
    rate_limits as Dictionary[String, Float]
    subscription_count as Integer
    message_count as Integer
    last_activity as Float
    is_active as Boolean

Type BroadcastSubscription is Dictionary with:
    subscription_id as String
    subscriber_id as String
    topic_id as String
    subscription_type as String
    filter_criteria as List[Dictionary]
    qos_requirements as Dictionary[String, Any]
    delivery_mode as String
    subscription_time as Float
    last_delivery as Float
    message_count_received as Integer
    is_active as Boolean
    acknowledgment_required as Boolean
    retry_policy as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type BroadcastMessage is Dictionary with:
    message_id as String
    topic_id as String
    publisher_id as String
    sequence_number as Integer
    broadcast_time as Float
    expiration_time as Optional[Float]
    message_type as String
    priority as String
    payload as Any
    headers as Dictionary[String, String]
    delivery_guarantees as List[String]
    delivery_status as Dictionary[String, String]
    acknowledgments as Dictionary[String, Dictionary]
    retry_count as Integer
    max_retries as Integer

Type BroadcastChannel is Dictionary with:
    channel_id as String
    name as String
    topics as List[String]
    subscribers as List[String]
    channel_type as String
    created_time as Float
    owner_id as String
    configuration as Dictionary[String, Any]
    statistics as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    health_status as String
    last_health_check as Float
    routing_rules as List[Dictionary]

Type BroadcastDelivery is Dictionary with:
    delivery_id as String
    message_id as String
    subscriber_id as String
    topic_id as String
    delivery_time as Float
    delivery_status as String
    delivery_attempts as Integer
    acknowledgment_time as Optional[Float]
    error_details as Optional[String]
    retry_scheduled as Boolean
    next_retry_time as Optional[Float]

Type BroadcastMetrics is Dictionary with:
    total_topics as Integer
    total_subscribers as Integer
    total_messages_sent as Integer
    total_messages_delivered as Integer
    total_messages_failed as Integer
    average_delivery_latency as Float
    peak_throughput as Float
    current_throughput as Float
    error_rate as Float
    subscription_churn_rate as Float
    last_updated as Float

Note: Topic Management Functions
Process called "create_broadcast_topic" that takes name as String and namespace as String and creator_id as String returns BroadcastTopic
Process called "configure_topic_access" that takes topic as BroadcastTopic and access_rules as Dictionary returns BroadcastTopic
Process called "set_topic_retention_policy" that takes topic as BroadcastTopic and retention_time as Float and max_messages as Integer returns BroadcastTopic
Process called "deactivate_topic" that takes topic as BroadcastTopic returns BroadcastTopic

Note: Subscription Management Functions
Process called "create_subscription" that takes subscriber_id as String and topic_id as String and subscription_type as String returns BroadcastSubscription
Process called "add_subscription_filter" that takes subscription as BroadcastSubscription and filter_condition as Dictionary returns BroadcastSubscription
Process called "set_subscription_qos" that takes subscription as BroadcastSubscription and qos_requirements as Dictionary returns BroadcastSubscription
Process called "activate_subscription" that takes subscription as BroadcastSubscription returns BroadcastSubscription
Process called "deactivate_subscription" that takes subscription as BroadcastSubscription returns BroadcastSubscription
Process called "update_subscription_statistics" that takes subscription as BroadcastSubscription and delivery_time as Float returns BroadcastSubscription

Note: Message Broadcasting Functions
Process called "create_broadcast_message" that takes publisher_id as String and topic_id as String and payload as Any returns BroadcastMessage
Process called "broadcast_message" that takes message as BroadcastMessage and subscriptions as List[BroadcastSubscription] returns List[BroadcastDelivery]
Process called "broadcast_with_acknowledgments" that takes message as BroadcastMessage and subscriptions as List[BroadcastSubscription] and timeout_seconds as Float returns Dictionary
Process called "retry_failed_deliveries" that takes original_deliveries as List[BroadcastDelivery] returns List[BroadcastDelivery]

Note: Channel Management Functions
Process called "create_broadcast_channel" that takes name as String and owner_id as String returns BroadcastChannel
Process called "add_topic_to_channel" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel and topic_id as String returns BroadcastChannel
Process called "add_subscriber_to_channel" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel and subscriber_id as String returns BroadcastChannel
Process called "remove_subscriber_from_channel" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel and subscriber_id as String returns BroadcastChannel
Process called "check_channel_health" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel returns Dictionary

Note: Filtering and Routing Functions
Process called "message_matches_filters" that takes message as BroadcastMessage and filters as List[Dictionary] returns Boolean
Process called "evaluate_broadcast_filter" that takes filter as Dictionary and message as BroadcastMessage returns Boolean
Process called "apply_routing_rules" that takes channel as BroadcastChannel and message as BroadcastMessage returns List[String]
Process called "evaluate_routing_rule" that takes rule as Dictionary and message as BroadcastMessage returns Boolean

Note: Metrics and Monitoring Functions
Process called "create_broadcast_metrics" returns BroadcastMetrics
Process called "update_broadcast_metrics" that takes metrics as BroadcastMetrics and operation as String and value as Float returns BroadcastMetrics
Process called "calculate_delivery_latency" that takes delivery as BroadcastDelivery returns Float
Process called "generate_broadcast_report" that takes metrics as BroadcastMetrics and time_window as Float returns Dictionary
Process called "calculate_broadcast_performance_score" that takes metrics as BroadcastMetrics returns Float

Note: Utility Functions
Process called "generate_topic_id" that takes namespace as String and name as String returns String
Process called "generate_subscription_id" that takes subscriber_id as String and topic_id as String returns String
Process called "generate_unique_id" returns String
Process called "generate_sequence_number" that takes topic_id as String returns Integer
Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float
Process called "get_current_timestamp_ms" returns Integer
Process called "string_from_integer" that takes number as Integer returns String

Note: Delivery Management Functions
Process called "create_delivery_record" that takes message as BroadcastMessage and subscription as BroadcastSubscription and delivery_time as Float returns BroadcastDelivery
Process called "deliver_message_to_subscriber" that takes message as BroadcastMessage and subscription as BroadcastSubscription returns Dictionary
Process called "calculate_retry_time" that takes delivery as BroadcastDelivery returns Float
Process called "count_successful_deliveries" that takes deliveries as List[BroadcastDelivery] returns Integer
Process called "count_failed_deliveries" that takes deliveries as List[BroadcastDelivery] returns Integer
Process called "count_acknowledgment_required_deliveries" that takes deliveries as List[BroadcastDelivery] returns Integer
Process called "wait_for_acknowledgments" that takes message_id as String and timeout_seconds as Float returns List[Dictionary]
Process called "get_pending_retries" that takes deliveries as List[BroadcastDelivery] returns Integer
Process called "attempt_delivery_retry" that takes delivery as BroadcastDelivery returns BroadcastDelivery

Note: Filter Evaluation Functions
Process called "evaluate_content_filter" that takes filter as Dictionary and payload as Any returns Boolean
Process called "evaluate_header_filter" that takes filter as Dictionary and headers as Dictionary returns Boolean
Process called "evaluate_priority_filter" that takes filter as Dictionary and priority as String returns Boolean
Process called "evaluate_publisher_filter" that takes filter as Dictionary and publisher_id as String returns Boolean
Process called "evaluate_time_filter" that takes filter as Dictionary and broadcast_time as Float returns Boolean
Process called "evaluate_routing_condition" that takes condition as Dictionary and message as BroadcastMessage returns Boolean

Note: Health and Recommendations Functions
Process called "generate_channel_health_recommendations" that takes issues as List[String] returns List[String]

Note: Export all types and functions
Export Type BroadcastTopic
Export Type BroadcastSubscription
Export Type BroadcastMessage
Export Type BroadcastChannel
Export Type BroadcastDelivery
Export Type BroadcastMetrics 